<h1>Pagination</h1>
<h2 class="docs-md__h2">Usage</h2>
Pagination can be used like this:
{{#docs-demo as |demo|}}
  {{#demo.example name="docs-demo-ax-pagination.hbs"}}
  {{ax-pagination
    currentPage=pageNum
    pagesCount=10
    onChange=(action (mut pageNum))
  }}
  {{/demo.example}}
  {{demo.snippet "docs-demo-ax-pagination.hbs"}}
{{/docs-demo}}
<code>currentPage</code>, <code>pagesCount</code> and <code>onChange</code> attributes can also be bound to query parameters.
<a href="https://github.com/offirgolan/ember-parachute">emper-parachute</a> can be used to simplify dealing with query parameters in Ember.